      "name": "Hemolysis model credibility — literature-based evidence",
      "description": "A systematic review of published CFD hemolysis studies was conducted, drawing on 14 peer-reviewed papers that applied the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law damage model to centrifugal blood pumps. The reviewed literature collectively demonstrates that CFD predictions of relative hemolysis index are consistent with reported experimental trends across comparable operating conditions. This body of evidence is considered sufficient to establish confidence in the model form and parameterisation adopted for the FDA generic pump geometry.",
